Version: 0.0.2
Simon Wilper
2013-05-25
2013-03-31
2006-08-23

The first unit should be the SI Unit of that particular group and is
represented by factor 1.  All factors of the subsequent units if multiplied by
will result in the SI Unit.

Use the transform attribute to perform more complex transformation of the
values.
-->

<units>

  <!-- volumes - relative to base SI unit cubic metre -->
  <group id="vol" desc="Volumes">
    <unit id="cubicmetre" type="factor" value="1" />
    <unit id="liter" type="factor" value=".001" />
    <unit id="gallon" type="factor" value="3.785412">
      <info>
        <![CDATA[The gallon (abbreviation "gal"), is a measure of volume that
        was used in many parts of Western Europe and is still used in the
        United States. Historically its value differed depending on locality
        and commodity. In most localities it has been replaced by the litre,
        but three variants in current use: the imperial gallon (≈ 4.546 L)
        which since metrication is used colloquially in the United Kingdom and
        semi-officially within Canada, the United States (liquid) gallon (≈
        3.79 L), and the lesser used US dry gallon (≈ 4.40 L). The gallon, be
        it the imperial or US gallon, is sometimes found in other
        English-speaking countries. Source: <a
          href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallon">Wikipedia</a>]]>
      </info>
    </unit>
    <unit id="pint" type="factor" value=".4731765" />
  </group>

  <!-- distance - relative to base SI unit m (meter) -->
  <group id="dist" desc="Distances">
    <unit id="meter" type="factor" value="1" />
    <unit id="centimeter" type="factor" value=".01" />
    <unit id="millimeter" type="factor" value=".001" />
    <unit id="kilometer" type="factor" value="1e+3" />
    <unit id="feet" type="factor" value=".3048" />
    <unit id="inches" type="factor" value=".0254" />
    <unit id="miles" type="factor" value="1609.344" />
    <unit id="feet_inches" type="special" value=".0254" pattern="([0-9]+)'? ?- ?([0-9]+)&#34;?">
      <subunit id="feet" multiply="12" />
    </unit>
  </group>

</units>
